      "npcs": [
        {
          "id": "archivist_wren",
          "x": 16,
          "y": 7,
          "name": "Archivist Wren",
          "dialogue": [
            {
              "lines": [
                "You came all this way to the last lit window in the world, and you want to know about the Maw. Everyone does, eventually.",
                "I've spent forty years reading what the Progenitors left in the salt. Come back when you've stood in front of the Maw. Then I'll tell you the first true thing.",
                "It won't comfort you. The true things out here never do."
              ],
              "when": {
                "flags_none": [
                  "bonewhite_truth1"
                ]
              },
              "set_flags": [
                "bonewhite_truth1"
              ]
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "You've silenced it. Good. Now the truth I promised.",
                "The Progenitors weren't monsters. That's the horror of it. They were us \u2014 people who woke every morning terrified for everyone they loved, in a world that was already ending around them.",
                "Something was coming. We don't know what; the salt doesn't say. But they decided that to protect everyone, they would weaponize life itself. Grow soldiers from gentle things. Just until the danger passed.",
                "The danger never passed. The weapons outlived the reason for them. And the Progenitors, protecting everyone, became the only thing left worth protecting everyone FROM."
              ],
              "when": {
                "flags_all": [
                  "bonewhite_truth1"
                ],
                "flags_none": [
                  "bonewhite_truth2"
                ],
                "heart_defeated": "the_maw"
              },
              "set_flags": [
                "bonewhite_truth2"
              ]
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "You know it all now. Every factory you've judged, you were judging them. Every core you've grafted, you were them, for a moment.",
                "The question the salt leaves me \u2014 the only one \u2014 is whether knowing is enough to make you stop where they couldn't."
              ],
              "when": {
                "flags_all": [
                  "bonewhite_truth2"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "The Maw is the oldest of the six. The first womb, in the first region we killed. It remembers a purpose none of the others do.",
                "Stand before it. Then come back to me. There are things I can only say after you've felt it breathe."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "keeper_alms",
          "x": 25,
          "y": 7,
          "name": "Ring-Keeper Alms",
          "dialogue": [
            {
              "lines": [
                "It's turning again in the Flats \u2014 the one place we thought too dead to relapse. Someone found the green you grew and the machine beneath it. Go finish what you woke."
              ],
              "when": {
                "relapsed": [
                  "the_maw",
                  true
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "You unmade the first womb. The Flats are quiet as the day they died \u2014 but that's the thing, they were already dead. You just made it honest."
              ],
              "when": {
                "verdict": [
                  "the_maw",
                  "Purge"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "You woke the Maw gentle and the salt is BLOOMING, rider \u2014 white gone to green in a place that forgot green. And I am so afraid of how much I want it to last."
              ],
              "when": {
                "verdict": [
                  "the_maw",
                  "Reseed"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "The oldest machine answers to you now. The Progenitors' own first engine, in your hand. Wren could tell you how that story ends. Ask her. Please ask her."
              ],
              "when": {
                "verdict": [
                  "the_maw",
                  "Bind"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "You've earned the deepest thing in my vault. Progenitor-work, pulled whole from the salt. It was built to protect everyone. Carry it better than they did."
              ],
              "when": {
                "flags_none": [
                  "bonewhite_gift"
                ]
              },
              "set_flags": [
                "bonewhite_gift"
              ],
              "give_grafts": [
                "progenitor_aegis"
              ]
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "Lastlight's the final ring before the Maw. The ante here is everything, because out here everything is already half-lost."
              ],
              "set_flags": [
                "bonewhite_keeper"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
